{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"4905","heading":"List of approved species","label":"4905 List of approved species","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/ch69","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Listing","label":"a Listing","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"One year after , and periodically thereafter, the Secretary shall, after notice and an opportunity for public comment, publish in the Federal Register a list of species of exotic birds that are listed in an Appendix to the Convention and that are not subject to a prohibition or suspension of importation otherwise applicable under section 4904(a), (b), or (c) of this title.October 23, 1992","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Manner of listing","label":"2 Manner of listing","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/a/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fa%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the countries of origin from which the species may be imported; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/a/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fa%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"if appropriate, the qualifying facilities in those countries from which the species may be imported.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Bases for determinations","label":"3 Bases for determinations","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/a/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/a/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fa%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"use the best scientific information available; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/a/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/a/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fa%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"consider the adequacy of regulatory and enforcement mechanisms in all countries of origin for the species, including such mechanisms for control of illegal trade.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Captive bred species","label":"b Captive bred species","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the species is regularly bred in captivity and no wild-caught birds of the species are in trade; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the species is bred in a qualifying facility.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Non-captive bred species","label":"c Non-captive bred species","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/c/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fc%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the establishment of a scientific authority or other equivalent authority;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/c/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fc%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the requirements of Article IV of the Convention with respect to that species; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/c/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fc%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"remedial measures recommended by the Parties to the Convention with respect to that species.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/c/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fc%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"provides for the conservation of the species and its habitat and includes incentives for conservation;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/c/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fc%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"ensures that the use of the species is biologically sustainable and maintained throughout the range of the species in the country to which the plan applies at a level that is consistent with the role of the species in the ecosystem and is well above the level at which the species might become threatened with extinction; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/c/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fc%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"addresses factors relevant to the conservation of the species, including illegal trade, domestic trade, subsistence use, disease, and habitat loss.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The management plan is implemented and enforced.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/c/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s4905/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs4905%2Fc%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The methods of capture, transport, and maintenance of the species minimizes the risk of injury or damage to health, including inhumane treatment.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
